{
  "texts": [
    "Pre-peer review screening consists of a number of checks, including format checks, plagiarism detection, and checking of language quality.",
    "In many cases, if a paper does not satisfy these checks, or fails in the initial editorial screening, it will be \"desk rejected.\"",
    "If the paper passes this stage, reviewers will be matched to the manuscript to enable peer review.",
    "For manuscript screening, AI tools have made good progress in automating tasks such as format checks.",
    "Journals and conferences impose various format rules for submissions-e.g., page limits, paper size, margins, font size, line spacing, paper structure, as well as section heading, figure, table, and reference styleswhose compliance needs to be checked."
  ]
}